&quot;Pregnant with her sixth baby, &quot;Rosa,&quot; a 36-year-old Hispanic woman, decided enough was enough. Her husband wouldn't have a vasectomy, and other birth control methods either were unreliable, made her feel sick, or required her husband's cooperation. After much soul searching, she decided to be sterilized right after she gave birth -- the easiest time, when it could be done in the same hospital visit. <br>
